parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fogging of dual glazed windows can significantly reduce visibility, making driving hazardous and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Fogging or misting on the driver and passenger side windows
reduced visibility
inability to see outside mirrors
difficulty changing lanes.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Failure Due to Caliper Pin Corrosion
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the caliper pins can cause the brakes to fail, leading to extended stopping distances or complete loss of braking ability, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal must be depressed completely to the floor to stop the vehicle
the vehicle continues to move when the brake pedal is depressed
the brakes feel spongy or soft
the brakes require repeated pumping to stop the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Failure Due to Hydraulic System Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hydraulic brake system can cause the brakes to fail, leading to extended stopping distances or complete loss of braking ability, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal must be depressed completely to the floor to stop the vehicle
the vehicle continues to move when the brake pedal is depressed
the brakes feel spongy or soft
the brakes require repeated pumping to stop the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster display can cause the driver to be unaware of the vehicle's gear position, leading to potential accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The instrument cluster display is blank or unresponsive
the gear indicator is not displaying the correct gear
other indicators in the display window above the steering wheel are not functioning.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Refrigerator Overheating and Electrical System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The overheating of the refrigerator can cause a short circuit in the electrical system, leading to a fire hazard, and potentially causing damage to other electrical components.
symptoms: The refrigerator is overheating
the electrical system is shorting out
the reset electrical plug in the bathroom and generator switch are malfunctioning
the water heater and microwave are not functioning due to electrical failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The accumulation of moisture between the two pieces of glass in the windows can cause fogging, mineral buildup, and reduced visibility, which can lead to accidents or difficulties while driving, especially in low-light conditions.
symptoms: Fogging or misting on the inside of the windows
moisture accumulation between the two pieces of glass
mineral deposits or streaks on the windows
reduced visibility through the windows
especially in mirrors.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fogging or delamination of windows can significantly reduce visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when changing lanes or merging with traffic.
symptoms: Windows fog up or delaminate
reducing visibility
especially on the passenger side mirror
making it difficult to change lanes or merge with traffic.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Defective window manufacturing can lead to premature fogging or delamination, compromising driver visibility and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Windows fog up or delaminate shortly after replacement
reducing visibility
especially on the passenger side mirror
making it difficult to change lanes or merge with traffic.
